    dc:creator "Roháćek, Jindřich; Barber, Kevin N." ;
    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "Nearctic Anthomyzidae: a monograph of Anthomyza and allied genera (Diptera)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272884>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272891>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272893>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272897>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272899> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272884>
    dc:description "Figs 106–109. Holotype males of the Nearctic species of the Arganthomyza duplex group. 106 – A. acuticuspis Roháček & Barber, 2013; 107 – A. bivittata Roháček & Barber, 2013; 108 – A. duplex Roháček & Barber, 2013 (all laterally); 109 – A. bivittata, head and thorax dorsally. Photo by J. Roháček. Adapted from ROHÁĆEK & BARBER (2013: Figs 1, 3, 5, 6)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4272884/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272891>
    dc:description "Figs 125–127. Wings of the Nearctic species ofArganthomyza. 125 – A. acuticuspis Roháček & Barber, 2013, paratype male, wing length 2.5 mm (USA: New Mexico); 126 – A. bivittata Roháček & Barber, 2013, paratype male, wing length 2.8 mm; 127 – A. duplex Roháček & Barber, 2013, paratype male, wing length 2.6 mm (both Canada: Ontario). Photo by K. N. Barber. Adapted from ROHÁĆEK & BARBER (2013: Figs 167–169)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4272891/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272893>
    dc:description "Figs 128–130. Arganthomyza bivittata Roháček & Barber, 2013, paratype male (Canada: Ontario). 128 – genitalia, laterally; 129 – external genitalia, caudally; 130 – gonostylus, lateroventrally (widest extension). Scales = 0.1 mm. For abbreviations see p. 11. Adapted from ROHÁĆEK & BARBER (2013: Figs 82–84)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4272893/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272897>
    dc:description "Figs 136–138. Arganthomyza bivittata Roháček & Barber, 2013, paratype female (Canada: Ontario). 136 – postabdomen, dorsally; 137 – the same, ventrally; 138 – the same, laterally. Scale = 0.2 mm. For abbreviations see p. 11. Adapted from ROHÁĆEK & BARBER (2013: Figs 90–92)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4272897/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272899>
    dc:description "Figs 139–145. Arganthomyza bivittata Roháček & Barber, 2013, paratype female (Canada: Ontario). 139 – female genital chamber and apex of postabdomen, laterally; 140 – spermatheca; 141, 142 – ventral receptacle, whole laterally (141) and apex ventrally (142); 143 – spermatheca; 144 – internal sclerites, laterally; 145 – the same, ventrally. Scales = 0.1 mm (Fig. 139) and 0.05 mm (others). For abbreviations see p. 11. Adapted from ROHÁĆEK & BARBER (2013: Figs 93–99)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4272899/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

